    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nCython should infer the item type of comprehensions, if possible, as a specialisation of the container type. For example:\n```cython\nx: list[int] = …\nresult = [ (a, a+1) for a in x ]\nprint(cython.typeof(result)\n```\nshould print `list[tuple[int, int]]` in the best case, but should at least show that `result` is a list of tuples.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
